items.title: Thunderbirds eclipse record-breaking $10M mark for local charities
items.summary:
The Thunderbirds, hosts of the Waste Management Phoenix Open Presented by The Ak-Chin Indian Community, raised a record $10,147,441 for local charities through proceeds raised from the 2017 tournament, Thunderbirds Big Chief Andy Markham announced today at Phoenix Children’s Hospital.  This is the highest single-year charitable donation in tournament history, breaking last year’s record totalâ€¦ Read More â†’
